<TITLE> 40 taken to HC board for detention extension </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 16 (bdnews24.com)  Forty people were produced before the High Court's detention advisory board Thursday for a decision about whether their detention should be extended. They include former state minister Salahuddin Ahmed and former lawmakers Mosaddak Ali Falu and Mufti Shahidul Islam. They were produced under tight security before the three-member advisory board of Justice Ali Asgar Khan, Justice Md Abdul Matin and a home ministry official. It could not however be immediately known whether their detention orders were extended as the matter was kept secret. bdnew
